            <title>[LUCENE-3224] bugs in ByteArrayDataInput</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3224</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;ByteArrayDataInput has a byte[] ctor, but it doesn&apos;t actually work (some things like readVint will work, others will fail due to asserts).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is it doesnt set things like limit in the ctor... I think the ctor should call reset()&lt;br/&gt;
Most code using this passes null to the ctor to initialize it, then uses reset(), instead they could just call ByteArrayInput(BytesRef.EMPTY_BYTES) if they want to do that.&lt;br/&gt;
finally, reset()&apos;s limit looks like it should be offset + len&lt;/p&gt;</description>
